  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Sudam Prabhakar Achat versus The State of Maharashtra pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_3_897_903','2025INSC378'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SUDAM PRABHAKAR ACHAT<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF MAHARASHTRA </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 3 S.C.R. 897</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 378</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010003862025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : BHUSHAN RAMKRISHNA GAVAI<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, AUGUSTINE GEORGE MASIH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose as to whether the conviction u/s.302 IPC could be converted into s.304 Part I or Part II IPC. Headnotes&dagger; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; ss.304 Part I, 300 exception IV, 302 &ndash; Culpable homicide not amounting to murder &ndash; Alteration of conviction to a witnesses &ndash; Reliability &ndash; Quarrel on account of previous enimity between the accused persons and the deceased who were brothers &ndash; Upon confrontation, the co-accused and his son-appellant became aggressive, and the co-accused armed with axe and the appellant armed with stick<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 21-03-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 641/2024</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Case Partly allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_3_897_903','2025INSC378','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view